1. Introduction

SmartRail is an AI-powered Railway Management System designed to improve passenger experience and railway operational efficiency. The system predicts train delays using Machine Learning, provides smart ticket reallocation, real-time train tracking, and an AI chatbot for passenger assistance.

This manual explains how to install, configure, and use SmartRail for both passengers and administrators.


2. System Requirements

Hardware

Processor: Intel Core i5 or higher
RAM: Minimum 8 GB
Storage: Minimum 5 GB free space

Software

Operating System: Windows 10/11, macOS, or Ubuntu 20+
Python 3.11 or higher
Node.js 18 or higher
PostgreSQL 14 or higher
Redis 6 or higher
Git

3. Installation and Setup

Step 1 — Clone the Repository

Open terminal and run:
git clone https://github.com/khushal45-ops/SmartRail-.git
cd SmartRail-

Step 2 — Backend Setup

Create and activate a Python virtual environment:

Windows:
python -m venv .venv
.venv\Scripts\activate

macOS/Linux:
python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate

Install Python dependencies:
pip install -r requirements.txt

Step 3 — Configure Environment Variables

Copy the example environment file:
cp .env.example .env

Open .env and set the following values:
APP_NAME=SmartRail API
DATABASE_URL=postgresql+psycopg2://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/railway_db
REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379/0
SECRET_KEY=your-secret-key-here
CORS_ORIGINS=["http://localhost:5174"]

Step 4 — Setup Database

Create a PostgreSQL database named railway_db and run migrations.

Step 5 — Train the ML Model

python app/ml/train_model.py

This will read datasets from the Dataset/ folder, train the Random Forest model, and save it to models/delay_model.pkl.

Step 6 — Start Backend Server

python -m uvicorn main:app --reload --port 8000

Backend runs at: http://localhost:8000
API Documentation: http://localhost:8000/docs

Step 7 — Start Frontend

Open a new terminal window:
npm install
npm run dev

Frontend runs at: http://localhost:5174


