6. ML Delay Prediction — How It Works

When you click "Predict Delay" on any train's Delay Analysis tab:


The frontend sends the train number and current station code to the backend API.
FastAPI receives the request at POST /api/trains/predict-delay.
The backend loads the trained Random Forest model from models/delay_model.pkl.
Input features are encoded using saved LabelEncoders from models/encoders.pkl.
The model predicts delay in minutes based on 9 features including historical delay percentages, route distance, and running days.
The predicted delay and confidence level (85%) are returned and displayed on screen.


Model Performance:


Algorithm: Random Forest Regressor
R2 Score: 93.21% accuracy
Average prediction error: 14.58 minutes



7. Troubleshooting

Problem: Backend not starting
Solution: Make sure PostgreSQL and Redis are running. Check .env file has correct DATABASE_URL and REDIS_URL.

Problem: "Failed to predict delay" error
Solution: Make sure models/delay_model.pkl exists. If not, run: python app/ml/train_model.py

Problem: Frontend shows blank screen
Solution: Make sure backend is running on port 8000. Check CORS settings in .env.

Problem: Login not working
Solution: Clear browser localStorage and try again. Use demo credentials: passenger@smartrail.com / pass123

Problem: npm run dev fails
Solution: Run npm install first to install all Node.js dependencies.


8. API Reference

The backend provides the following REST API endpoints:

POST /api/auth/register — Create new user account
POST /api/auth/login — Login and receive JWT token
GET /api/trains/ — List all trains
POST /api/trains/predict-delay — Predict delay for a train at a station
PUT /api/trains/{id}/status — Update train status (Admin only)
GET /api/tickets/ — List tickets
POST /api/tickets/reallocate — Request ticket reallocation
POST /api/chat — Send message to AI chatbot
GET /api/analytics/summary — Get dashboard statistics
GET /api/analytics/delay-trends — Get delay trends for last 7 days
WS /ws/train/{id} — WebSocket for live train status
WS /ws/dashboard — WebSocket for live dashboard stats

Full interactive API documentation available at: http://localhost:8000/docs


